# Project Goal

Migrate DS5 Construction from Next.js to Astro with pixel-perfect visual match, better performance, and minimal client-side JavaScript.

# Main Rules

- Do not redesign the site.
- Keep layout, spacing, colors, typography, images, and responsive behavior as close as possible to the current Next.js version.
- Prefer `.astro` components over React components.
- Use React only when real interactivity is required.
- Do not convert the site into an SPA.
- Keep Astro output static unless server logic is required.
- Preserve existing URLs where possible.

# Tech Stack

Use:

- Astro
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Content Collections
- Astro Image
- Vercel deployment

Avoid:

- unnecessary React
- Framer Motion by default
- large animation libraries
- heavy client-side state
- unnecessary API routes
- unnecessary npm packages

# Architecture

Use this structure:

```txt
src/
├─ components/
│  ├─ common/
│  ├─ sections/
│  └─ cards/
├─ content/
│  ├─ services/
│  └─ projects/
├─ layouts/
├─ pages/
├─ styles/
└─ utils/
